==Japanese==

===Etymology===
Japanese kanji 左様なら / kana さようなら :

* 左様なら / さようなら (''sayōnara'' or ''sayounara'') means "if it be thus", "if it is to be that way", "so let it be"
** 左様 / さよう (''sayō'' or ''sayou'') means "thus, that way"
*** 左 / さ (''sa'') means "that"
*** 様 / よう (''yō'' or ''you'') means "appearance, way" (from Chinese ''jiang'')
** なら / なら (''nara'') means "if, if it be"

===Interjection===
'''さようなら''' (''sayōnara'')

